# Patch: Log the per-expert load distribution as "load/min", "load/max" and quantiles
#
# Goal:
#   See, at a glance, the spread of expert load across the whole model. For an expert e in an
#   MoE layer, load_e = (tokens routed to e) / (tokens in the batch). With top-k routing the
#   per-layer loads sum to topk, so perfect balance is topk/num_experts per expert; load/max
#   -> 1.0 means a layer funnels (almost) every token to one expert, load/min -> 0.0 means an
#   expert is (nearly) dead. The quantiles load/p10..load/p90 fill in the shape of the
#   distribution between those extremes (load/min == p0, load/max == p100).
#
# What this patch does:
#   1. megatron/core/transformer/moe/router.py (TopKRouter._log_expert_imbalance):
#      reuses the already-reduced global_tokens_per_expert / total_num_tokens that the
#      expert-imbalance monitor computes, and saves to the MoE tracker:
#        - expert_load.max()/.min() under "load/max" / "load/min" (reduce_op max/min);
#        - the full expert_load vector under "load" (reduce_op "collect"), from which
#          track_moe_metrics derives the pooled quantiles "load/p10".."load/p90".
#      Monitor-only (detached); piggybacks on the same aux-loss routing gate as
#      expert_imbalance (patch 0003), so it is logged for aux_loss/seq_aux_loss/global_aux_loss
#      routing even at moe_aux_loss_coeff == 0.
#   2. megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_utils.py: teaches the MoE layer-wise tracker a
#      per-metric "reduce_op". Default "sum" is byte-for-byte the old behavior.
#        - "max"/"min": seed slots with -/+inf, accumulate across micro-batches with max/min
#          (not +=); clear resets to -/+inf; track_moe_metrics aggregates across MoE layers
#          with max()/min(). Untouched dense layers keep their -/+inf seed and are ignored, so
#          the value is the true extreme over all experts of all MoE layers.
#        - "collect": store the full per-expert vector per layer (shape num_layers x
#          num_experts), accumulate across micro-batches with += and clear to 0. In
#          track_moe_metrics the rows are scaled by loss_scale (1/num_microbatches) to the mean
#          per-expert load, dense layers (all-zero rows) are dropped, the remaining experts of
#          all MoE layers are pooled, and torch.quantile reports each entry of _LOAD_QUANTILES
#          as "load/pXX". (Quantiles are not an associative scalar reduction, hence storing the
#          distribution rather than a per-layer scalar the way max/min do.)
#
#   "load/*" flow to TensorBoard and W&B automatically via track_moe_metrics (it logs every
#   tracker entry by name); the "load/" prefix puts them all in their own panel.
#
# Scope / caveats:
#   Like "expert_imbalance" (patch 0003) these names are not added to track_names, so
#   reduce_aux_losses_tracker_across_ranks does not cross-rank-reduce them: the value is the
#   logging rank's local view. This is exact for the launcher's config (TP=PP=CP=EP=1,
#   data-parallel only, every layer MoE); with PP>1 it would only cover the logging rank's
#   pipeline stage. Quantiles are pooled over the logging rank's experts only.
#
# How to find the right location in a future Megatron version:
#   router.py: the save_to_aux_losses_tracker("expert_imbalance", ...) call added by 0003.
#   moe_utils.py: save_to_aux_losses_tracker / clear_aux_losses_tracker / track_moe_metrics.
#   To change which quantiles are logged, edit the _LOAD_QUANTILES tuple in moe_utils.py.
#
# Applied to: Megatron-LM core_v0.16.1 (commit 55ac7082), on top of patches 0001-0003.
#
diff --git a/megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_utils.py b/megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_utils.py
index 61c7f8d2c..c477da764 100644
--- a/megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_utils.py
+++ b/megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_utils.py
